  "texts": [
    "Clinical examination: conduct a thorough clinical examination to assess the size, extent, and characteristics of the CGCG.",
    "Imaging studies: panoramic radiographs and cone-beam CT scan or MRI biopsy: incisional biopsy or fine-needle aspiration biopsy to confirm the diagnosis and obtain a histopathological assessment.",
    "Histopathological examination: presence of giant cells and characteristic features of CGCG.",
    "Treatment options: the choice of treatment depends on the size, location, and aggressiveness of the CGCG.",
    "Surgical excision is the primary treatment option."
  ],
